  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Baoding Ecosystem Restoration and Livelihood  Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Baoding Ecosystem Restoration and Livelihood Development Project is a collaboration between Heifer China, the Sichuan Haihui Poverty Alleviation Service Center and Baoding agricultural authorities. The purpose of this project is to help mountainous villages improve their environment and living conditions using Heifer&#x2019;s Values-Based Holistic Community Development model. The project will provide 100 families in Shuishitang Village with 200 beef cattle and 80 families in Xiliujing Village with 480 sheep to empower farmers to establish their own small animal production businesses. Another 260 families will benefit through Heifer&#x2019;s Pass on the Gift process within the project period. Local authorities will fund the building of bio-gas digesters and cattle shelters, and they will provide training on natural resources conservation and ecosystem restoration. Within five years, the two participating communities will find a sustainable way to better their lives and environment through systematic community capacity building.</narrative>
  </description>
